1 G. Any insurance or indemnity coverage shall be obtained or
2 provided solely from funds available in the shared risk pool
3 authorized by Section 85.34B of this title. Any coverage limits
4 shall be based on the liquidity of the shared risk pool resulting
5 from the annual payments made pursuant to Section 85.37 of this
6 title and any interest accrued thereon, after deduction of such sums
7 as may be necessary to pay all overhead and administrative expenses
8 associated with administering the pool.
9 H. Any limited indemnity coverage provided for errors and
10 omissions pursuant to the provisions of this subsection shall only
11 cover errors or omissions made by a board member, official, employee
12 or volunteer of any entity specified in subsection C of this section
13 occurring after the effective date of this act.
14 I. The State of Oklahoma is not liable, directly or indirectly,
15 for the errors and omissions of any board member, official, employee
16 or volunteer of any entity specified in subsection C of this section
17 in the performance of his official duties pursuant to law. The
18 State of Oklahoma is not liable, directly or indirectly, for the
19 negligence of any entity specified in subsection C of this section.
20 J. In providing risk management services for any entity
21 specified by subsection C of this section or any such board member,
22 official, employee or volunteer of such entity, it is the intention
23 of the Legislature to provide coverage solely to the extent of
